const faqs = [
  { q: "Is Smeg the same company as Bertazzoni?", a: "Different companies, common family origin. <b>Smeg Spa</b> was founded in 1948 by Vittorio Bertazzoni Jr. in Guastalla, Italy — a different branch of the broader Bertazzoni family from the one that runs the Bertazzoni appliance brand (founded 1882 by a different family line). The two companies are now independent, with separate engineering, separate manufacturing, separate US distribution (Smeg US based in Oakhurst NJ; Bertazzoni US based in Englewood Cliffs NJ), and separate parts chains. For LA customers deciding between Smeg and Bertazzoni, these are distinct Italian brands despite the shared family name in their origin stories. We verify which at diagnostic before sourcing parts — Smeg parts route through Smeg US distribution; Bertazzoni through Bertazzoni US distribution." },
  { q: "What are Smeg's wall oven product tiers — Victoria vs Classic vs Dolce Stil Novo?", a: "Three distinct Smeg wall oven lines serving different aesthetic positioning. <b>Victoria Series</b> — Smeg's retro-styled collection with the signature rounded vintage aesthetic that has made the brand famous; Victoria wall ovens carry the distinctive curved door + colorful finish signatures (pastel colors, bold Italian hues). <b>Classic Series</b> — Smeg's clean modernist design language; more subdued + contemporary than Victoria's retro emphasis. <b>Dolce Stil Novo</b> — Smeg's premium tier with upscale Italian design language + premium control platform + higher-end finish quality. Each tier targets different aesthetic buyers within LA's design-forward kitchen renovation market. Service: mechanical components (bake elements, convection fans, sensors) largely interchange across Smeg tiers with tier-specific variants; aesthetic trim (handles, panel finishes, glass door features) is tier-specific and carries tier-specific parts." },
  { q: "Does Smeg make small appliances? Do you service those?", a: "Smeg is well-known in the US for its retro-styled small appliances — toasters, kettles, stand mixers, espresso machines, refrigerators in signature Smeg colors. These are a separate scope from built-in wall oven service. Our coverage focuses on Smeg built-in appliances (wall oven + range + cooktop + built-in refrigerator + dishwasher + range hood) rather than small countertop appliances. Small-appliance service routes through different channels (manufacturer warranty, authorized small-appliance repair specialists) and isn't part of our service coverage. For LA customers with Smeg small appliances, the manufacturer's customer service portal or small-appliance-specific retailers are the right service channel." },
  { q: "What does Smeg wall oven repair cost in LA?", a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Smeg wall oven service at premium Italian-tier pricing: Victoria / Classic / Dolce Stil Novo bake element $360-$580 depending on tier-specific variant; convection fan motor $400-$640; control board (tier-dependent) $480-$820; temperature sensor $280-$440; door hinge $320-$520; door glass $440-$720 (Victoria curved-door glass specialty quoted separately); thermostat $340-$540; self-clean door-lock motor $280-$460; Victoria curved-door hardware + aesthetic trim quoted individually reflecting specialty parts chain. Smeg US Oakhurst NJ distribution 5-10 days common parts, 7-14 days Italian-factory-specific specialty components + aesthetic tier-specific trim." }
];

const schemaJsons = [
