  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Smeg — Italian design-forward, Guastalla since 1948</h2>
    <p>Smeg Spa was founded in 1948 in Guastalla, Italy by Vittorio Bertazzoni Jr. (a different branch of the broader Bertazzoni family from the line that runs the Bertazzoni appliance brand founded in 1882). The two companies now operate entirely independently with separate engineering, separate manufacturing, separate US distribution, and separate parts chains — shared family history, distinct operational structures. Smeg's distinctive global positioning is Italian design-forward aesthetic with multiple tier options across the lineup.</p>
    <p>For LA service, Smeg parts run through Smeg US Oakhurst NJ distribution. Common service parts typical 5-10 day lead; Italian-factory-specific specialty components + aesthetic tier-specific trim 7-14 days. Victoria Series curved-door glass and aesthetic trim carry the longest typical lead times reflecting the specialty nature of the retro signature design.</p>
    <p><b>Scope note</b>: Our coverage is Smeg built-in wall oven only. Smeg's small countertop appliances (toasters, kettles, stand mixers, espresso machines) are out of scope — those route through different service channels (manufacturer warranty + authorized small-appliance retailers).</p>
  </div></section>

